Border crossing points will be open only to pedestrians.
Starting from Saturday, every day from 8 am until 8pm, five border crossings will be open.
The possibility of borders being opened to vehicle transport will be the subject of special bilateral agreements on security, trade and energy, said the president.
Last year in August Maduro ordered the closure of the border, in a response to the Colombian militant attack on the Venezuelan border patrols.
