"Facebook" declares a fight against ad blockers.
The world's most used social network Facebook has broadcast a warning shot, leading to believe that ad-blocking, by using special tools, it is not acceptable and all users are going to have to watch advertising.
Special ad blocker popularity is growing, but it means that companies, whose main source of income is from advertising, are suffering from decreased revenue.
Facebook acknowledges that advertising can be annoying, but expresses that users will have to learn to live with them anyway.
However, they will be provided with tools to be able to choose themselves what type of materials appear, reports the BBC.
"As people have more options for control, we'll start sending ads to those using ad-blocking software," said Facebook advertising business vice president Andrew Bosworth.
In other words, users will be able to choose what type of ads they see by selecting the brands and the sectors that they find interesting.
"People do not like to see ads that they are not interested in or that interfere with their enjoyment of content," added Bosworth.
Ad blocking tools on mobile devices usually do not work, of which Facebook has the largest attendance, but the resulting banner exposure reduction just in terms of money is measured in billions.
According to BBC information, advertising blockers are used by about 200 million people.
As reported in the previous business year quarter Facebook advertising revenues were 6.2 billion US dollars or 5.55 billion euros.
It should be noted that this is not the first time that Facebook has been actively involved in determining what network users see in their news feeds.
As one of the last steps Facebook has just started to take action to remove from news feeds, or at least limit "loud" titles, behind which actually lie "empty" messages.
